## 💻 SQL Commands

### CREATE — Build the Structure

Used to create a new **database** or **table**.

```sql
-- Create a database
CREATE DATABASE school;

-- Use the database
USE school;

-- Create a table
CREATE TABLE students (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    email VARCHAR(150) UNIQUE
);
```

---

### INSERT — Add Data

Used to add new rows into a table.

```sql
-- Insert a single row
INSERT INTO students (name, age, email)
VALUES ('Alice', 20, 'alice@email.com');

-- Insert multiple rows
INSERT INTO students (name, age, email)
VALUES
    ('Bob', 22, 'bob@email.com'),
    ('Charlie', 21, 'charlie@email.com');
```

---

### ALTER — Modify Structure

Used to **add, modify, or drop** columns in an existing table.

```sql
-- Add a new column
ALTER TABLE students ADD COLUMN phone VARCHAR(15);

-- Modify a column's data type
ALTER TABLE students MODIFY COLUMN age SMALLINT;

-- Rename a column
ALTER TABLE students RENAME COLUMN phone TO mobile;

-- Drop a column
ALTER TABLE students DROP COLUMN mobile;
```

---

### DELETE — Remove Data

Used to remove **rows** from a table.

```sql
-- Delete a specific row
DELETE FROM students WHERE id = 1;

-- Delete all rows (keeps table structure)
DELETE FROM students;
```

> ⚠️ Always use `WHERE` with DELETE — without it, **all rows get deleted!**

