## 📊 Quick Comparison Table

| Feature         | RDBMS                    | NoSQL                        |
|-----------------|--------------------------|------------------------------|
| Structure       | Tables (rows & columns)  | Documents, Key-Value, Graph  |
| Schema          | Fixed                    | Flexible / Dynamic           |
| Query Language  | SQL                      | Varies (JSON-based, etc.)    |
| Scaling         | Vertical                 | Horizontal                   |
| Best For        | Structured data          | Unstructured / Big data      |
| Examples        | MySQL, PostgreSQL         | MongoDB, Redis, Cassandra    |

---

| Key Type      | Created By  | Based On          | Changes? |
|---------------|-------------|-------------------|----------|
| Natural Key   | Real world  | Actual data       | Possible |
| Surrogate Key | Database    | Auto-generated ID | Never    |
| Primary Key   | You decide  | Either type       | No       |
| Foreign Key   | Relationship| Another table's PK| Depends  |
